# The generated spec must stay LF in the working tree on every platform, so its
# byte-match drift test holds. Without this, core.autocrlf=true would check it
# out as CRLF on Windows while generateSpec() emits LF, failing the test.
docs/spec.md text eol=lf

# The generated variety board is byte-pinned to generateVariety() by its drift test;
# keep it LF in the working tree on every platform so the byte-match holds (as spec.md).
docs/variety.md text eol=lf

# The gauntlet bot documents are frozen scoring inputs: benchmark-config's
# INPUT_HASH is the sha256 of their (LF) file text. Pin them to LF so the hash
# guard holds on every platform — else core.autocrlf=true checks them out as
# CRLF on Windows, changing the hashed bytes and failing the guard test.
bots/*.json text eol=lf
